This paper primarily focuses on the security and privacy aspects of cloud storage services, which falls under the category of "Computer Security and Cryptography" (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of a software system, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE) aspects. The paper also mentions the use of a directory-based key hierarchy, which is a data structure commonly used in distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of out-of-band channels for authentication, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
